      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activity geometry, material, loading, and boundary conditions are representative of the COU; any differences between validation and COU contexts are identified and their impact bounded.",
      "rationale": "The validation activity uses the identical non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw geometry, material lot, and ASTM F1717 test configuration as the COU. The validation is therefore directly representative of the COU context. The sole difference — single test condition versus the broader clinical loading envelope — is captured in the Test conditions factor above and acknowledged as a gap. Achieved level meets required level."
