    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level for a Medium model risk, Medium model influence, Medium decision consequence COU. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is offset by the direct equivalency of validation geometry and loading to the COU, the multi-laboratory experimental dataset, and the conservative acceptance bounds applied to all QoI comparisons. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support regulatory submission of the FEA-based compression-bending predictions for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
